The paper proposes a framework for interactive agent modeling, which involves learning to probe the environment and the target agent to enhance the accuracy of the agent model. This involves two learning processes: imitation learning and curiosity-driven reinforcement learning. The paper focuses on the application of this framework in multiple tasks, including collaboration and competition. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper involves learning processes and modeling. The other likely sub-categories are cs.RO (Robotics), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper involves interactions between agents and the environment.
